pageContext.claim: “I never even spoke to him. I'd like to congratulate you on your win. He just became the president of Ukraine. Let's impeach him for that. These people are sick.”
pageContext.analysis: This is false. Trump had spoken to Volodymyr Zelensky once before -- when he called him on April 21, 2019 to congratulate him on his victory. The July call that led to Trump's impeachment came months after that initial conversation.
